content: Hey team! Just pushed the latest changes to the audio-video-calls branch
Nice! I'll pull and test it out
Great work! How's the call quality?
Pretty solid. Using Amazon Chime SDK for the WebRTC implementation
That's awesome. Any issues with the integration?
A few edge cases with participant management but mostly stable
Are we handling group calls too?
Yes! Both direct and group calls are working
That's a huge milestone ðŸŽ‰
Definitely! What's next on the roadmap?
We need to work on the chat message search feature
Good point. Right now we can only scroll through history
I can take that on. Thinking ElasticSearch or just DynamoDB queries?
DynamoDB GSI should work for now. Keep it simple
Agreed. We can always upgrade later if needed
Makes sense. I'll draft a design doc
Perfect. Also noticed some UI bugs in the profile sidebar
The one that slides from the left?
Yeah, the z-index isn't working right on mobile
I saw that too. Let me fix it
Thanks! Also, we should discuss the notification system
Right, we're using AppSync Events for real-time but no push notifications yet
SNS + FCM would work well for mobile push
And for desktop we could use web push API
Let's prioritize that for next sprint
Agreed. I'll add it to the backlog
Speaking of sprints, how are we doing on the timeline?
Pretty good. Chat and calls are mostly done
File sharing is still pending though
True. That's a critical feature for student collaboration
I'm thinking S3 for storage with presigned URLs
That would work. What about file size limits?
Maybe 50MB for free tier users, 200MB for premium?
Sounds reasonable. We can always adjust based on usage
What file types should we support?
PDF, images, documents, and maybe code files?
Let's whitelist common types and scan for malware
Good idea. AWS has some antivirus scanning options
I'll research that
Perfect. Moving on to the whiteboard feature...
Oh yeah! The virtual whiteboard for collaboration
That's going to be challenging but really cool
I was looking at Fabric.js or Excalidraw
Excalidraw is open source and has great real-time features
How would we handle the real-time sync?
AppSync Events again, sending delta updates
Makes sense. Keep the architecture consistent
What about saving the whiteboard state?
Store as JSON in DynamoDB, export as PNG/SVG for archiving
That's smart. Users can download their work
Btw, how's the authentication holding up?
Cognito is solid. No issues so far
Are we doing email verification?
Yeah, required for account activation
And we added MFA as optional for security-conscious users
Nice. What about password reset?
Cognito handles that automatically via email
We should add social login eventually
Google and maybe GitHub?
That would make onboarding easier for students
Definitely on the roadmap. Now about the AI summary feature...
Oh that's the one using AWS Bedrock right?
Yeah! Super useful for catching up on long conversations
Exactly. Users can get a summary of what they missed
Which model are we using?
Claude 3.5 Sonnet from Bedrock
Great balance of quality and cost
How do we handle the context window?
Fetch the last 100 messages and send to the model
With prompt engineering to focus on key points and action items
That's really smart. Students will love that
Especially for group project chats
Exactly the use case we're targeting
What about rate limiting on the AI calls?
Good question. Those API calls aren't free
Maybe 10 summaries per day for free users?
And unlimited for premium?
That could work as a monetization strategy
Let's track usage and adjust limits based on data
Sounds like a plan
Quick question about the database schema
What about it?
I'm curious too
Are we using single-table design or multiple tables?
Multiple tables for now. Users, Conversations, Messages, Calls
Easier to reason about for a team project
Makes sense. We can always refactor later if needed
Right. Premature optimization is the root of all evil
ðŸ˜„ Classic Knuth quote
We're building solid foundations though
Definitely. The real-time messaging is super responsive
AppSync Events was a great choice
Way better than polling or long-polling
And WebSocket connections scale really well
Have we done any load testing?
Not yet but we should before launch
I'll set up some basic stress tests
Thanks! We should test with 100+ concurrent users
That would simulate a decent campus rollout
Agreed. Let's aim to have everything tested by end of week ðŸš€
